# Moonu Chatwoot MVP Rules

This project evaluates Chatwoot as a white-label or embedded omnichannel layer on a
Moonu-like PBX platform. See `.specify/memory/constitution.md` v1.1.0.

Do not modify Chatwoot source code unless a task or decision record explicitly authorizes it.

Treat Chatwoot as an external self-hosted service. All Chatwoot access goes through the adapter.

**Adapter-first** for all external systems: Chatwoot, Meta/WhatsApp (future), telephony APIs,
billing providers. No direct vendor API calls outside adapter packages.

**Moonu Simulator owns**: customers, subscriptions, simulated phone numbers, simulated PBX
extensions, billing status (simulated), Chatwoot mappings, omnichannel activation state.

**Chatwoot owns**: conversations, inboxes, contacts, agent conversation handling, WhatsApp
workflows, omnichannel support UI.

Prefer small, demoable vertical slices. Every feature must validate the omnichannel hypothesis.

When external API behavior is unknown: mock first, mark manual/research, write TODO—never
invent behavior. Spikes must end with: works / does not work / unknown / requires credentials.

**Demo seed customers** (required): Clínica Exemplo, Escritório Contábil Alfa, Loja Boa Luz.

**UI status labels** must distinguish: automated, manual_setup_required, mocked,
not_implemented, failed, connected.

**Locale**: Brazilian SMB / WhatsApp-heavy examples in product copy; English-first codebase.

No secrets in code. No real WhatsApp credentials required for local demo. No real PBX/SIP.

Every feature must have:
- user-facing behavior
- data model impact
- acceptance criteria
- basic test coverage (core domain + adapter + tenant isolation)

Definition of Done: see constitution. Update docs/decisions/ for architectural choices.
